Relational Operators are used to compare values.
< > = <= >=  are used in relational operators.
Here we will use a relational operator along with the WHERE clause.

1. Create Database
CREATE DATABASE CompanyDB;

2. Use Database
USE CompanyDB;

3. Create Employee Table (EMP_INFO)
CREATE TABLE EMP_INFO (
    EMP_ID INT PRIMARY KEY,
    NAME VARCHAR(50),
    SAL INT,
    JDATE DATE
);

4. Insert Sample Data
INSERT INTO EMP_INFO (EMP_ID, NAME, SAL, JDATE) VALUES
(101,'RAM',20000,'2022-10-22'),
(102,'SITA',30000,'2021-05-10'),
(103,'RAHUL',40000,'2020-07-15'),
(104,'AMIT',75000,'2019-03-20'),
(105,'PRIYA',25000,'2022-10-22'),
(106,'KIRAN',18000,'2023-01-11');

5. Display Table Data (Optional)
SELECT * FROM EMP_INFO;

Example Output
