These are mostly used with the WHERE clause to filter records.

Q1. Employee details having salaries less than 25,000
SELECT * FROM EMP_INFO WHERE SAL < 25000;

Q2. Employee details having salaries less than or equal to 25,000
SELECT * FROM EMP_INFO WHERE SAL <= 25000;

Q3. Employee  details having salaries equal to 75,000
SELECT * FROM EMP_INFO WHERE SAL = 75000;

Q4. Employee details those are not getting 40,000
SELECT * FROM EMP_INFO WHERE NOT SAL = 40000;

Alternative (more commonly used):
SELECT * FROM EMP_INFO WHERE SAL <> 40000;

Q5. Employee details whose name is RAM
SELECT * FROM EMP_INFO WHERE NAME = 'RAM';

Q6. Employee details who joined on 22nd Oct 2022
SELECT * FROM EMP_INFO WHERE JDATE = '2022-10-22';